<item>
            <title>[FELIX-400] pom resources are not correctly processed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-400</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Resources listed in &amp;lt;build&amp;gt;&amp;lt;resources&amp;gt; are not correctly processed into the Include-Resource directive, the includes and excludes are ignored, and if you use &amp;lt;directory&amp;gt;${basedir}&amp;lt;/directory&amp;gt; you get an out of bounds exception&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The code for processing resources is here&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/maven/plugins/trunk/maven-resources-plugin/src/main/java/org/apache/maven/plugin/resources/ResourcesMojo.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/maven/plugins/trunk/maven-resources-plugin/src/main/java/org/apache/maven/plugin/resources/ResourcesMojo.java&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;it should be probably factored out for reuse&lt;/p&gt;</description>
